  "prompt": "Is it possible to change names in savings a/c?",
  "response": "Yes, it is possible to change names in a savings account, but the process can vary depending on the specific circumstances and the bank's policies. Here are some common scenarios:\n\n1. Name change due to marriage:\n- Provide marriage certificate\n- Submit identity proof with new name\n- Visit bank branch with original documents\n\n2. Name change due to legal reasons:\n- Submit government gazette notification\n- Provide court order for name change\n- Update documents like Aadhaar, PAN card\n\n3. Correction of spelling or minor errors:\n- Submit supporting documents\n- Fill name change form\n- Provide proof of identity and address\n\nGeneral requirements:\n- Original documents\n- Filled application form\n- Identity and address proof\n- Recent photographs\n- Existing account details\n\nProcess steps:\n- Contact bank branch\n- Submit necessary documents\n- Pay any applicable fees\n- Get account updated\n\nImportant notes:\n- Each bank has specific procedures\n- Some banks might require in-person verification\n- Processing time varies\n- Keep all original documents ready\n\nRecommended: Directly contact your bank's customer service for precise, current guidelines specific to your account.",
